<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Car makers across the UK and the EU are urging politicians to secure a Brexit trade deal to avoid 'catastrophic' losses. </p>

<p>Tariffs would threaten the production of 3m EU- and UK-built cars and vans over the next five years. </p>

<p>This would mean losses of up to £84billion for the European automotive sector, and threaten thousands of jobs. </p>

<p>Warning: Tariffs would threaten the production of 3m EU- and UK-built cars and vans over the next five years</p>

<p>Speaking for the whole industry, Mike Hawes, of the UK's Society of Motor Manufacturers and Traders, said: 'These figures paint a bleak picture of the devastation that would follow a No Deal. </p>

<p>'The shock of tariffs and other trade barriers would compound the damage already dealt by a global pandemic and recession, putting businesses at risk.'</p>
